  "size": "1024x1536"
}

{
  "prompt": "An ironic Soviet-style propaganda poster featuring an American oilfield worker in red, white, and blue tones. The worker is muscular, smoking a cigarette, with visible tattoos (including a prison-style portrait). He holds a large pipe wrench crossed with a sledgehammer, replacing the traditional hammer and sickle. The background is simplified with strong geometric rays and minimal elements, evoking classic communist aesthetics. The slogan reads 'FROM EACH ACCORDING TO THEIR DAY RATE, TO EACH ACCORDING TO THEIR OVERTIME.' The style is bold, vintage, and tongue-in-cheek, blending patriotic and Soviet design elements.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A bold and ironic propaganda-style poster inspired by Soviet-era aesthetics, but using American colors (red, beige, blue). The poster features a rugged, tattooed oilfield worker wearing safety glasses and a hard hat. He's holding a large pipe wrench crossed with a crowbar in place of a hammer and sickle. His arms are covered in skull and flame tattoos. He has a cigarette hanging from his mouth and a tough expression. The top slogan reads: 'FROM EACH ACCORDING TO THEIR DAY RATE,' and the bottom reads: 'TO EACH ACCORDING TO THEIR OVERTIME.' The background is simplified with sunburst rays in red and beige, giving it a clean but powerful look.",
